  "description": "Voice communication over wire: Bell electromagnetic telephone, Edison carbon microphone, magneto ringers, manual switchboard (cord board) exchanges, and Strowger automatic step-by-step exchange (1889). The Strowger exchange eliminates human operators, enabling private dialing. Capacity: 100-10,000 subscriber lines per exchange. Loading coils extend effective range from 30 km to 150+ km.",
